The paper deals with optimization problems on matroids and generalized polymatroids, which are fundamental topics in theoretical computer science and discrete mathematics. The use of hypergraphs and element multiplicities suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), while the approximation algorithm for the metric Many-Visits TSP involves combinatorial optimization (cs.GT) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also presents a new algorithmic technique that may be of interest to researchers in approximation algorithms (cs.DM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
